item.title: What the heck is this
item.dc:creator: @Java_Is_My_Bitch Java Is My Bitch™
item.description:
@Java_Is_My_Bitch wrote:

No.

When you put your server lets say on a server status page, every X minutes it checks it the server is still online. How does it check? By Trying to connect to it. Just fix it in server class, like:

if(connectingHost.equalsIgnoreCase(“flamebox.org”)) {
println(“Checking If The Server Is Online”);
}

If you block em, the status page wouldn’t know that your server is online, thus it showing your server being inactive in the status page.
